rComments: He was a wonderful professor with pouring of humanity out of his veins. He taught so passionately and loved his students.  You were wonderful and will always be remembered. Rest in Peace dear Professore.  I am me today because of you. Thank you. Grazie Mille.
Long lectures, speaks in monotone, wish I never took this class. Pray you get a good TA, class average was a C- ! Lots and lots of reading, expects you to know every single detail for exams!
Excellent Professor. Informal and participatory lecture style (small class). Can not say enough good things about Prof. Pugliese, very much enjoyed his class and mentoring.

HONESTLY--the best professor at UTM!!! There is no professor that could stand up to this man. He is absolutely great! Helpful, kind, sinicere and a hard worker. He comes up with the best ideas for film class and theatre class. If you need an elective--HE IS the best and as long as you work, he will not hesitate to give you an A!!
